00:05:06.486 --> 00:05:13.406
Cleopatra and her brother, Ptolemy XIII, should get married and be joint rulers.

00:05:14.916 --> 00:05:20.776
This might sound unusual to us, but it was the Ptolemaic tradition for

00:05:20.786 --> 00:05:25.796
siblings to marry and have children, so that the royal blood was “pure”.

00:05:27.256 --> 00:05:33.626
The problem was, in Cleopatra’s case, that she didn’t really get on with her brother, plus she

00:05:33.626 --> 00:05:41.536
was far more talented than he was, and this sibling rivalry culminated in a full scale civil war.

00:05:42.946 --> 00:05:48.206
Shortly before this, there was also civil unrest on the other side of the Mediterranean.

00:05:48.936 --> 00:05:54.796
Rome was split into two factions: that of Julius Caesar and that of Pompey.

00:05:56.206 --> 00:06:01.626
After a decisive battle in Greece, The Battle of Pharsalus, where Pompey’s forces were

00:06:01.626 --> 00:06:08.416
defeated, Pompey was forced to flee to Egypt, where he thought he would be welcomed with

