00:08:28.566 --> 00:08:31.826
The 21-year-old Egyptian queen presented herself to

00:08:31.826 --> 00:08:36.206
Caesar and he was immediately drawn in by her charm.

00:08:37.316 --> 00:08:42.436
But this wasn’t, reportedly, merely that she was a beautiful woman.

00:08:43.131 --> 00:08:49.091
It was because she was a fascinating person, a great conversationalist, supremely intelligent,

00:08:49.511 --> 00:08:55.541
and someone the Roman clearly felt an immediate connection with and attraction for.

00:08:57.121 --> 00:09:02.781
We have no record of what Cleopatra felt for Caesar, but the two quickly

00:09:02.781 --> 00:09:07.491
became lovers and allies, with Caesar supporting her against her brother.

00:09:08.971 --> 00:09:13.781
Caesar attempted to negotiate a settlement with Ptolemy XIII, allowing

00:09:13.781 --> 00:09:18.211
for Cleopatra and Ptolemy to rule jointly, but it was rejected.

00:09:19.101 --> 00:09:25.601
Ptolemy raised an army and laid the palace to siege, with Caesar and Cleopatra inside it.

00:09:27.131 --> 00:09:29.741
